               <head>Biblical fragments</head>


               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379" rend="visible">


                  
                  <summary>Biblical fragments ('Second Gaster Bible') with masorah magna and parva
                     .</summary>


                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>


                  
                  <msItem rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379">


                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="37v"/>


                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tana"kh </title>


                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">תנ"ך</title>


                     
                     <decoNote type="other">Numerous golden rosettes and medallions between the
                        lines, the text columns and in the margins, in colours and gold.<locus n="34r"/>
                     
                     </decoNote>


                     
                     <note>
                        
                        <p>The manuscript contains Genesis 34:5-35:3, 39:19-43:15, 44:16-37:25,
                           49:3-50:26; Exodus 1:1-12:3, 39:24-39:36, 39:40-40:15; Leviticus
                           14:3-16:8, 19:23-20:18, 23:5-23:33; Numbers 2:24-3:26, 13:7-14:8,
                           14:40-15:31, 20:28-21:29; Deuteronomy 1:11-1:31, 3:14-4:10, 11:29-12:20,
                           16:11-17:15, 19:5-20:15, 26:5-28:23, 30:16-31:21. </p>
                        
                        <p>See <ref target="Gaster_1901" type="number">350</ref>, <ref target="Narkiss_1984" type="page">23</ref>, <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">20-21</ref>. </p>
                     
                     </note>


                  
                  </msItem>


               
               </msContents>


               
